caption: Started off a little slow with service but it picked up quickly. Good food and very good bottomless mimosa!

Went here after a long day of walking. The food was delicious and it came out quick, there was no wait to be seated, and did I mention it was delicious? It was. Soooo good. Highly recommend the Mac n cheese (made with smoked gouda, YUM) and the all american burger. They have happy hour all day, lots of local beers, and great service. The ambience is 10/10 and they have immaculate and visually pleasing bathrooms! I had an absolutely fantastic time! There is street side parking, but it's scarce so I'd be ready to walk. Five minutes away from the metro, too!
Superb ambience and super affable service. The food was fresh and enchanting. Will definitely recommend this restaurant to anyone. Convenient rates and generous meals. Great job.

I really appreciate the precautions taken for COVID. Unlike before, customers can't walk up to the omelette/waffle bar-you have to order your omelette and waffle on an order sheet and give it to your server; smart!  The omelette was great! I was surprised that the waffle automatically came with chicken. They DID say chicken and waffles. Maybe I didn't read it right. Hey, I'm not about to complain about fried chicken.  Maybe I am because unfortunately the chicken was not well seasoned at all. I just moved it to the side and the waffle was tasty though. It makes the most sense to do the all-you-can-eat/bottomless option. We only ate one portion of each and were full, but it's worth it Bc it would've been more À la carte.

The people who work here are truly some of the friendliest and warmest people that I have encountered during my years here in DC. They all make an effort to get to know you while you’re in line and are extremely knowledgeable of their food. The managers take the time to work on the little details, whether cleaning off the glass doors, or the tables in the restaurant and this work ethic shows time after time. I love the salads that they offer and the people make the experience so personal. I have made a connection here and I feel extremely valued as a customer every time I step foot in the door. Without a doubt you should stop in and try it sometime! Personal recommendation: Mexican Caesar, it’s awesome!

Fantastic restaurant. Well managed and good food. Kale salad is very different and delicious. They finely chop Kale so is not hard to eat with just the right amount of fixins that act like a surprise in every bite. Ask for the Lincoln chair where Obama sat. Appropriately priced for good restaurant.
Great atmosphere!
Nice spot!  Very good wings!! Juan was an excellent waiter!
Great service!
Great place! Spacious. Staff was excellent! Service here is 2nd to none and very friendly. Food was fantastic. Prime rib was perfectly cooked and the smoked gouda mac n cheese was a winner.

Wonderful restaurant. The restaurant host saved our table for us as we were 45 minutes late for our reservation due to streets being closed off due to the huge celebration in town. My wife had a delicious New York strip and I had an awful chicken pot pie. Don't get the pot pie.
Moses our server was flawless, food was very good, and outside seating made for a perfect lunch , small flawless menu.
Our server Moses was really good. The made to order omelet and the chicken and waffle were very tasty. Really enjoyed the raspberry mimosas

Lincoln overall was a fair experience. I went for brunch with a friend. We were pretty hungry and ended up ordering a variety of things from their pretty small brunch menu. The food was decent. Brussel spouts were life. The server was a bit of a downer and may have soured the experience a bit. Don't think I would go back with so many other options around.

Good service and pretty decent menu. Type of place that seems high end but is pretty laid back so you don't feel out of place. Would absolutely go back. Due to the name and multitude of pictures of a bearded, unsmiling man I believe it is named after the sixteenth president of the United States.
Brandy took care of us and we give her a 200%
Food was fantastic and service was even better.  Was there by myself and the server was very personable and attentive.

I opted to try Lincoln’s summer restaurant week lunch menu and am glad I did. The mac and cheese appetizer/side was generously portioned and kept well even with takeout. The salmon on quinoa was just the right size, and the salmon was cooked perfectly (no one likes dry salmon!). For dessert, the chocolate fudge cake was a good choice if you love chocolate. It is definitely on the decadent end of the chocolate spectrum! When I arrived, I saw that there was a large bottle of hand sanitizer right outside of the front door and I waited a couple of minutes before the staff brought my order to me. The staff wore a mask and gloves. Hope to try other items next time!
Great mac n cheese

Fantastic brunch!  We were looking for a place to brunch and Lincoln is one of the few places open (thanks covid),  and they have just started serving brunch.  The food and service were Phenomenal!  Two of us got the unlimited brunch option that includes omelets, waffles, and bottomless mimosas.  Everything tasted excellent and George and the rest of the employees took excellent care of us.   Definitely get the short ribs in your omelet... it was amazing.... and banana pudding on waffles.... oh so so good.   We're definitely coming back for another brunch.  Super excellent value for the money!
Open night life
Exceptionally good food - had halibut tacos and cheeseburger. Up charges for sides not clearly indicated. Wait staff and other staff efficient and wonderful.
Good food and atmosphere
Food, service, & atmosphere great! One of my favorite restaurants I've tried so far. Will definitely go back again, on my next visit

Came here on a Sunday afternoon and place was bumpin! Good music and atmosphere, it's a little loud so it's hard to conversate but overrall good service and great food! I had the Lincoln Breakfast which included Eggs, Hashbrowns, biscuits and gravy, and chicken sausage and OJ. Very good, I will definitely be back here!

We walked in to very loud music for Sunday brunch but the DJ was sooo great mixing live! I think I read on his laptop "Phlipz", we need good music like this back in the scene. The the food is good but could be better. I'd come back just to hear this DJ!
Food was pretty good, ordering off the menu is sufficient. Buffet seems overpriced at $52. DJ was great, fun environment to be with friends, but left smelling smoky. They need to work in ventilation

My wife and I just happened to stop in, and we enjoyed it almost immediately. The staff was professional, the drinks were some of the best we've had in DC, and the establishment overall was immaculately clean and welcoming. We've been to many social/restaurants throughout DC and this was hands-down one of the best.. if you're in DC, stop by or you'll be missing out.
Fairly cheap eats for downtown. Simple, American dishes. Some chef inspired specials. Great happy hour menu (foods and drinks).
Loved it

A tapas restaurant, so the portions are a little smaller than usual. I would suggest getting at least three dishes for two people. The service was not stellar and they couldn't remember who ordered what drink at what table. We were constantly being asked if we had ordered certain drinks.

The food is awful. The atmosphere is nice. Maybe they can rent it out for events where you bring your own caterer? Good luck finding a place to park. Went for brunch on a Sunday and it's just not worth the price. The chopped fried chicken pieces was the most flavorful item they offered. Unseasoned hot water Shrimp and Zits (the grits I can only imagine to be animal feed) bottomless mimosas/Bellinis/Bloody Marys made primarily with cheap alcohol and not a drop of the fruit/veggie juices that makes them refreshing was sad. The omelet station had the ingredients that should have made a decent omelet, but only to get back to to the table to find it not palatable. The chopped chicken pieces and the waffle were the best items on the brunch buffet, definitely not worth the $52 they charge. Oh and they offer you two side items from their full menu to go with the brunch buffet. I chose applewood smoked bacon and a salad. The bacon was cooked to the point that it became charcoal and the bland salad was just spring mix with white balsamic dressing (oil and vinegar). All of the other side items mimicked the items offered on the buffet so choose wisely. I did hear that the chicken sausage was ok. Those in my party that ordered directly from the menu were also underwhelmed by what was presented to them as food. Also, don’t leave any personal items on the table to only go back to discover that they are long gone where the table busser, waiter, or patrons at adjacent tables take them as the spoils of war. As, I think back on it I should have had them play the tape as an overhead camera was in the area. In the end, it all makes sense because after the overall experience I could only come to the realization that you've been had from the moment that you walked through the door.
Tasty food and perfect service
Bar always has great service. Food is delicious and good happy hour.
Music and ambiance during lunch is worth it!
Restaurant week has introduced me to this great place.  The food was soooo good. The brussel sprouts are AMAZING!!!
Great drinks, even better prices. Happy hour is a must
A few vegan options. Very basic
Food was horrible, waiter sounded sarcastic the whole time, ambiance barely redeemed anything. There’s no wait for a reason.
Great Happy Hour spot! Responsive waitresses and a very good atmosphere.
Giving 1 star for the food but would give 4 for ambiance. Food was disappointing. Calamari looked and tasted like chicken sticks. If you go, stick with the burger.

The main draw to this place is the decor which is modern yet classic and very unique. The walls, light fixtures and table furnishings were all a site to see. The food is average at best. The wine selection was decent. Service could have definitely been better. I wouldn’t overpay for slightly below average food again but the decor is a draw.
Years later and still going strong. I enjoyed the lunch specials!
Visited during Winter Restaraunt Week. Staff was phenomenal- attentive, accommodating, and connected with us from the start. The three course dinner was delicious! Portion sizes were perfect!

Wes, our server,  did not disappoint.  He kept the unlimited bellinis,  mimosas,  and bloody Mary's flowing. I don't know who did the fried chicken but someone's southern grandmother had to be in the kitchen. The food was amazing and decor was eclecticly pleasing. Pennies everywhere. The DJ was on fire for a brunch.
Moonshine drink was great. Small plates were fine, normal DC spendy. Place was super loud and crowded on a Thursday night though.
Cool place for brunch. Paul (bartender) was super friendly and cool. Pricey but good buffet with chef
Had drinks and dinner at the bar. Food was good, drinks were solid. The bar tender made the night

Nice place for lunch,  various portions of a variety of different items,  easily layed out in columns on the menu.  Wait staff did a great job from describing the menu,  portion sizes,  to delivery of food and good follow up.

The ambiance is nice! I went today for lunch, and the food could have been better. I went a few months ago for happy hour though, and the food was great! It’s 4 stars at best, no more than that. Our waiter Scott, was also great! Very attentive, respectful, and made us feel like our business was appreciated!
Place was a bit of a mess, we had the lunch menu and it was ok. Our server was delightful though.
Very hip and very busy. Good food, great people.
Great staff
Foodie food for people who like choices! I loved the Amish chicken and the crem broule!!
Was here in 2013. A very nice restaurant.

Lincoln has a great atmosphere and was very relaxing. Our waiter/bartender did an amazing job and the speed of service was above par. Add to that the clean restrooms and happy hour and this place is hard to beat. Oh yeah, everything we ordered (mostly bar bites) was delicious.
Awesome restaurant 👍
Thanksgiving dinner just ok
Awesome Sunday brunch. Kinda costly but...
Great service and food was well made and presented. Recommend for a more upscale dining atmosphere.

Bottomless brunch on Sunday was lit! Great music played by the DJ. Wes our server was attentive and quick. The restaurant was clean, spacious and the the wall of pennies or water jugs and Mason jars as pendant lights adds a nice ambiance. You have to try the fried chicken it's delicious!!
So amazing , loved the ambiance.  It was kinda loud inside.  So for talking it was a little hard. However, the food , service and everything was great !

My husband and I went to celebrate our 20th year anniversary. The lunch was good and the cocktails amazing. The waitress gave us dessert on the house as a present. Everyone was nice. Will go back for sure!
Great atmosphere and there was no wait to sit down.
Great food and good service. They have a great happy hour.
Food is good, and that must beer is interesting and eclectic. Service is excellent.
Great food and historic atmosphere! Quick service and prices were affordable.
The food is good and can't complain about happy hour prices, but the staff could have been a bit more welcoming for a solo interloper :)

We enjoyed most of the aspects of this conveniently located restaurant. Pros: Amazing drinks. Had an Abe's Sour and it was fantatic . Probably the best Mac and cheese I have ever had. Our waiter, Wes, was a lot of fun.  Cons: The host was less than pleasent. Practically through our menus on the table. Just overall seemed bothered to be there. For $42, the fillet mignon could have come with more than just an bowl of arugula that was drowning in dressing. A nice pepper sauce or port sauce would have made it a better value. It was a good steak, just very bare and out of contrast with everything else on the menu.  Overall, I would come back for the drinks and Max and cheese and tryout the other dishes.
Great service and really good food. The Brussels sprouts were amazing.
Great food, fast & friendly service and nice ambience.  Ordered deviled egg appetizer and seasonal small plate of NY strip with broccoli and mushrooms.  Delicious!

Atmosphere and ambiance is second to none. Subtle use of pennies..😉 Female AfAm server was very cool as she single-handedly took care of our 13-person party and other tables. Menu selection was specific to our party, but the offerings were very diverse. The starters were great followed by very well executed entrees. Desserts were underwhelming, except for three chocolate fudge cake-- that little number will knock your socks off (and I'm not much of a chocolate guy). Overall, I would certainly return.

Very nice place with good atmosphere. Extremely kind waiters. Good choice of food and beverages. The American burger was excellent, so were the potatoes and the  dessert. Interesting selection of beers. Very good timing also: the right waiting-time to have a pleasant dinner.

Amazing shareable plates. Service was a bit slow to take our drink order, but once we placed our order, service was attentive and the food was great. The decor is fantastic too. One of Lincoln's speeches is written on one wall, there are pennies on the floor and other cool touches.

Went at the tail-end of happy hour and had a couple of great drinks and shareables...  the short rib poutine and mac and cheese were both absolutely fantastic. We couldn't stop raving. Great atmosphere and friendly bartenders. Great spot!
Loved it. Food a little pricey.
Expensive but the brunch food was delicious.
Love this place for brunch. Great selection of food and a dj too? 👍👍

(Translated by Google) Good service, friendly and helpful. The quality of the food is normal, quite neutral and that is why the price is not entirely appropriate. The site ok.  (Original) Buen servicio, amables y serviciales. La calidad de la comida está normal, bastante neutra y por eso el precio no es del todo acorde. El sitio ok.

Service was crazy fast. The food was just Ok though. The pork shoulder was super tender but didn’t have much flavor. The beans were under cooked to the point of being inedible. Flourless chocolate cake was good but the sauce was not. Given all the good restaurants in the area I would skip this one.

Awful experience.   Ordered a drink, 20 minutes later it had not arrived and our waiter had not been by to check on us.  Flagged down another waiter who said he would take care of it.  Ten minutes later still  no drink.  We went inside and asked for our check.  Five ninutes later a waitress appeared with the drink.  When the check came (brought by yet another waiter ) it showed two drinks.  We asked that one be removed and a fourth waiter said he had served us two drinks - which he then admitted was not true. Had to get the manager to resolve. Every server we encountered was either inattentive or rude.

I love the pennies on the bar and Abes's Moonshine is an excellent drink! Crafted cocktails and small plates make up the menu. Sleek decor and a very high end vibe permeate the building. Awesome place to go for lunch with some co workers or you could do dinner with your honey! Order deviled eggs and poutine for happy hour, they are delicious!  Pork shoulder with swiss chard and cannellini beans was hearty and hot the spot after a long day at work. I'll definitely be going back with friends!
(Translated by Google) Delicious food, excellent honey apple pie dessert  (Original) Deliciosa comida, excelente el postre honey Apple pie
The bartender here was crazy good! Food was amazing and came out quick. I cant wait to try the sunday brunch
Bit noisy and our waiter took about 20 minutes for my second beer!!!! Not to mention not getting what I ordered! But the NY strip streak was pretty good... so three stars.

Good concept with American tapas style menu. But I wasn't blown away by any particular dish (except the devilled eggs). The prime rib in particular was blah. Portion sizes were large for tapas. Definitely could have been satisfied with one dish.

Went to dinner around 7pm on a Thursday night, there were no lines.  Our waitress was friendly.  Tried brussel sprouts for the first time and loved it.  We also ordered the Pork Chop but it wasn't that good for our taste.  Kind of pinkish for pork.
Decent burger but bun was at least two days old. Waiter had a very indifferent attitude. I guess we just looked like tourist.
Awesome customer service, Daniel was great! Food was delicious!

Nice clean restaurant.  Was the only place on a Friday night that had no wait time for a table for two.  Everywhere else just north was about a 45 minute wait.  Rooms in the very back are are the loudest, main eating are inside is less noisy, and outdoor dining is quiet. Just depends on what kind of vibe you prefer. If you prefer quiet indoor dining, try to go during non-peak hours. The waitress said they were trying a new Fall menu. The pumpkin risotto was good. Very creamy. The shrimp deviled eggs are three deviled egg halves for $6.  Beautiful presentation on both dishes.

The drinks were great, the multiple food items had were all phenomenal, our dessert was divine and the service was exceptional!! Too bad we found this place on our last day in DC- otherwise we would have had multiple meals here!
A wonderful service oriented restaurant with delicious seasonal fares. Theodore, the manager, along with staff, are all attentive and go above and beyond. Highly recommended!
Happy hour is only at the bar and outside...which i thought was odd.  Food came out as it was ready, so i ate while my guests just looked on.  Overpriced for what you get.
Food was great but ordered drinks thinking they applied to their happy hour special advertised on the tables but they were full price. False advertising
A wonderful find.  Great food and atmosphere

From the moment we walked in our experience was amazing! Loved the staff and hear the executive chef Demetrio A Zavala is an amazing and personable gentleman. Don’t you just love that, I do! The brussel sprouts, mac and cheese and short ribs rock! Husband loved the steak burger!

Had trade association group dinner here.  Nice variety of specialty and regular cocktails. "Small" plates are enough if you want a light meal or could easily share a couple between 2 people.   Scott is a great waiter making good recommendations for good and drinks to meet individual tastes or customizing dishes like taking out dill where possible.   Great experience!  Would definitely go again.
The waiter Daniel was awesome, actually all of our wait staff was good.The buffet is pretty costly but just ok with regards to taste. I am glad I tried it but I may or may not return again.

I am visiting from Georgia and staying at the Westin and was looking for a restaurant nearby and stumbled upon this restaurant.  They didn't have any rice, which I am used to having with my salmon.  They didn't have any brocolli, which again I love to pair with my salmon.  I got bitten like crazy by mosquitoes sitting outside...the weather was amazing and so is the ambience.  But they get 5 stars.  Let me tell you why.  The food is DELICIOUS.  Everything that came was exquisite. Their deviled eggs are YUM...I ate one of each. The mac and cheese paired very well with the salmon, although the salmon comes with potatoes and green beans.  I was pleasantly surprised by the food and great service. Definitely returning at least one more time before I head back home.  PS: to get here from the Westin, turn right and just keep walking along the building without crossing any streets. There's also a 24 hour CVS along that route. You shouldn't walk more than 5 minutes.
My partner went to pick up takeout for us and he came back raving about his experience. Thank you, Daniel!
(Translated by Google) Nice  (Original) جميل
AMAZING FOOD LOVED THE SPECIAL, CAME DOWN WITH A COLD ON MY TRIP, THEY MADE ME SOME FRESH HOT CHICKEN SOUP, TO GO WITH MY MEAL, LOVED THE CHOOSE 3 SPECIAL , THANKS
Had their salmon special and watermelon and beet salad. Both were delicious!
Went in for drinks with my coworkers.  Reasonable prices and food I tried was good.  The calamari was presented in a new and unique way that I liked - cut lengthwise.  Worth a try.
Food was good. Didn't try any special drinks as it was a business lunch but nice atmosphere. Great brussel sprouts!
Great food, great alcohol selection, wonderful staff and atmosphere. A must-visit restaurant if you’re in the area!

We went here for restaurant week this summer, and will definitely be returning. We ordered the zucchini tots, the brussel sprouts, the shrimp and grits, the NY strip steak, and the lemon semifreddo.  For drinks we ordered the maple crusta, the lady lincoln, among others. All of the drinks and food were great. Street parking was also easy to find which is a nice random bonus.

Excellent food, amazing actually. The service is also perfect, very nice and funny waitress. A bit expensive, it cost us 130$ USD for a party of 4, it it worth it. Great ambiance and decoration, modern  and trendy with a touch of vintage. Easy reservation online, fast service. They have also a good selection of beer, which is not the case in many places in Washington DC. We also went there a second time during our trip.
so American place
Good food and good service.  The fish was perfectly cooked, but the burger Patty was placed directly on a untoasted bun, so it was soggy, but perfectly cooked.
Been here many times. Food, drinks and service are great! Recommend.

I have never been to this restaurant, so I can't comment on service  or ambiance. I ordered from them through a delivery service. I ordered the pineapple upside down cake and  a pulled pork sandwich. Those two items were over $30 dollars. The cake was a tiny round disk that was way too sweet  and dense. The sauce on the sandwich was too sweet and too salty.  Worst meal I ever ordered. Most of it went into the trash. I'll never order from there again.
The food was delicious. I had chicken and waffles  and my friend had the brunch buffet.  The atmosphere was lit and energetic. I look forward to going again when I am in the DC area.
Great service, reasonable prices and impressive menu selections.

The staff was unatentive, the food was mediocre and the portions were miniscule.  I paid $13 for 2 slivers of chocolate cake that maybe weighed less than 3 ounces.  It looks like they are cutting corners to stay in business.
Great happy hour cocktails.
Very nice place for Happy Hour, especially enjoyed the chicken sliders.
Great food, cool decor but it's pretty loud inside
The calamari fries were legit
Great service. Our lunch order took no time in getting served. The pulled pork sandwich I ordered was very good.

What better way to celebrate my favorite president!!! This trendy DC restaurant has a cool vibe- great place for business meetings or just hanging out with friends.  They have an incredible menu and friendly staff as well. Come for the brunch!
The atmosphere was great and our server was attentive, nice, friendly and courteous.

Great spot in DC, not super busy at dinner time, and we were seated and served immediately. Me and my wife had the Cheeseburger and lobster risotto respectively. Both of these dishes were delicious and prices are very reasonable.
I had the kale salad and the pan-seared scallops. Very good, and great service!

calimari quite chewy, lobster roll too toasty, one order wrong (of seven), strangely kept filling up my water like 1/3 of the way. food tasted good but they could work on plating. server was friendly enough.
Yummy

My first time here on Sunday past for my birthday brunch. As i waited for my party i sat at the bar. Spoke with a bar helper and he told me i had to wait for the bartender. I was there sitting for about 10 minutes. Three other individuals came in sat at the end of the bar (separate party from myself)and some how ended up receiving full service. Ordering drinks and food. I still hadn’t been acknowledged by the bartender. Until I let him know I had only been sitting there for 10 minutes.  It was only then he said oh they said you were waiting for a table. Ahhh I see, interesting.  Needless to say I did get a drink.  After being seated the waiter just dropped the menus in front of us. Mind you this is my first time. A few other with me as well. We clearly had to figure this out fast. There were a couple other things that didn’t sit well with me but no need to continue about that. Maybe this was one of these experiences that was just a coincidence. I don’t know.  Do I recommend this place I can’t really say.  Not to sure if I will try it again anytime soon.

Over the last three years during the TRB annual meeting, where tens of thousands of attendees gather in the DC area, our center has held alumni parties at this restaurant. It seems they have catered large groups (over 20) so many times that we have not had any problems about their service. Definitely, I look forward to next January’s meet up.
The food was absolutely well-prepared and accompanied by a professional, attentive waitstaff. I will be back!
Good atmosphere, the food was a bit hit or miss but you are given very nice portions. The service could have been better especially for the amount of gratuity that was charged.
Good food but too expensive for what you get. The $17 burger was child sized. Friendly staff and awesome interiors probably good place for drinks
Amazing food! Amazing service!
Great food and service
Very friendly. Walked right in with no wait. The food was amazing. Very easy walk from our hotel, Washington Plaza.
Very nice restaurant with a theme! Tasty food, good service and nice ambiance!
Great friendly service!  Yummy food
Great decor, good food.
I read the menu ahead of time online. When I got there, I was a little bit surprised that many of them were small plates. Everything tasted great though and the staff was really friendly!
Had beautiful surprise B-day brunch in April; great menu...
Ordered the NY strip salad for lunch really good, only change add field greens the arugula by itself a little over powering. Other then that this place is happening.
The staff members were very welcoming and friendly. The food and drinks were fantastic and the whole atmosphere was really nice.
The food was gpod, atmosphere was fun and youthful. But the prices were ridiculous!!! Seriously $41 for just a standard buffet? C'mon.....

I only got to sample the cocktails. However, they were nice takes on some old classics. The bartender was very candid with me that one of the cocktails hadn't turned out so good that night, and she made some good recommendations. Would return.

Everyone was so nice, friendly and helpful. I ate at the bar, and the bartender not only kept a cold beer in front if me, he gave great advice on what to order. The brussel sprouts were different yet excellent. The salmon was amazing.  The place was active; not bad for a rainy Tuesday night. I can't wait to go back!
Awesome for brunch!

Great atmosphere, great staff, very friendly & knowledgeable. The Sunday brunch was everything! So worth the $52. Looking forward to coming back again when I come back to D.C. Thanks for making the final to my weekend memorable.
Nice food,Nice place. Friendly staff.
Friendly staff. Good food. Pleasant atmosphere.
A great place for brunch!
Good food and good service, worth going
Good food and wine at fair prices. Chicken pot pie not to be missed. Nice ambience too!
Incredibly rude experience. Piss pour establishment.

Horrible service. Went w a large group for happy hour, we never got service until we asked for it, then server would bring drinks and never check on us again for refills unless we tracked him down, went on all our stay there, and at the end when complaining to manager he replied that he knows his people and that they work well.

Lincoln has a great atmosphere and was very relaxing. Our waiter/bartender did an amazing job and the speed of service was above par. Add to that the clean restrooms and happy hour and this place is hard to beat. Oh yeah, everything we ordered (mostly bar bites) was delicious.

Everything we had was delicious.  I highly recommend the Carrot and Ginger Soup, the Mac & Cheese, and the Deviled Eggs of all varieties. They were all just scrumptious! The dinner rolls were alsi particularly tasty. We came in for quick bites, so I can't comment on the entrees or salads. The only reason I didn't not give 5 stars is because the menu is a bit limited, but everything we had was absolutely excellent!
The rum punch is weak, and everything else is too expensive honestly.  Otherwise cool spot.
We went for brunch, it was so so. In my opinion it was not worth our bill. Needless to say we won’t go back, but the food was good enough.
Very good food. Fair prized for the area. Will come back.
Service was good the food delicious!
great place .. i really like the way of treatment .. wonderfull staff .. i do love that
On point menu reduced by so-so food prep. Our group of five had two items sent back to the kitchen. Good ambiance, except for tasteless and bizarre fetish-style decor in men's restroom.

Came here for brunch with a friend, and the experience was pretty awful all around. The bagel came dry and untoasted, and crab cake Benedict was cold. Waiters congregated among themselves and simply stared when we were trying to adjust the table out of the sun, but came every two minutes to try to take away our plates when we were not even done eating (this was not because anyone was waiting for table: half the place was empty). There was loud music that was more suitable for a Saturday night in club than Sunday morning in a brunch setting: we were told could not be turned down because they were from "DJ Speakers." We left vowing never to come back again.
American bar/restaurant with average food and service.

Visited this restaurant while exploring Washington DC from NY. My 10 y o son is allergic to fish, nuts and eggs. The waiter was informed. It took forever for my sons food to arrive since they were making sure there are no cross contamination and I was very grateful for that. The rest of the families dinner arrived pretty fast. We ate and were full but my sons meal still wasn’t ready. So he waited some more. While we were waiting I ordered French fries and my son ate some because he was so hungry. Few minutes later his lips swelled up. Apparently at this restaurant everything is fried in one oil! Everything!!! sea food, French fries, veggies, etc. So it triggered my sons allergic reaction. We rushed to the nearest hospital. I was really surprised that one oil is used for everything! Unbelievable! Very wrong! Even if there are no food allergies I believe sea food should be separate from everything else! We were very lucky we got to the hospital on time. And came back home to NY the following day. BTW, my husband paid for the dinner and left tips as well, they deducted my sons meal though. I think it would’ve been nice of them not to charge us at all!
Appetizers were tasty and very diffetent.  Exceptional service.  We were part of a happy hour gathering.  Great room.
